"13:11:22" : {s: 13, a: 11, w: 22, r: "", t: "وَإِذَآ", l: "إِذَا", lc: 409, tl: "wa-idhā", lb: "যখন",e: "And when", b: "এবং যখন", i: "dan jika", f: 130, rm: ""},
"13:11:23" : {s: 13, a: 11, w: 23, r: "رود", t: "أَرَادَ", l: "أَرَادَ", lc: 139, tl: "arāda", lb: "ইচ্ছা করা",e: "wills", b: "চেয়েছেন", i: "menghendaki", f: 18, rm: "to seek, ask a thing gently, search (for food), go to and fro in a pasture, go round about. iradatun - will, free will. mirwad - axle of a pully. rawada - to long after, desire, seduce, entice, seduce against the will (with an) as in 12:126. yuridu - he wishes, intends. It is used as an auxiliary verb as in 18:77. The word iradah is used for power and capacity with reference to subjugation as well as to option and choice. ruwaidan - for a little while, go gently (according to some grammarians the word is a diminutive form of which verbal noun is not in use, it is used as sing. plu. f. m.)."},
