"13:13:1" : {s: 13, a: 13, w: 1, r: "سبح", t: "وَيُسَبِّحُ", l: "سَبَّحَ", lc: 42, tl: "wayusabbiḥu", lb: "গুণকীর্তণ করা, পবিত্রতা ঘোষণা করা, তাসবীহ পাঠ করা",e: "And glorifies", b: "গুণগান করে", i: "dan bertasbih", f: 1, rm: ""},
"13:13:2" : {s: 13, a: 13, w: 2, r: "رعد", t: "ٱلرَّعْدُ", l: "رَعْد", lc: 2, tl: "l-raʿdu", lb: "বজ্র, গর্জন,",e: "the thunder", b: "বজ্র", i: "guruh", f: 1, rm: "to thunder/tremor, threaten of war, tremble/quiver/shiver/commotion occasioned by fear or cold, moved to and fro (e.g. a hill or heap of sand shaking and consequently pouring down)."},
"13:13:3" : {s: 13, a: 13, w: 3, r: "حمد", t: "بِحَمْدِهِۦ", l: "حَمْد", lc: 43, tl: "biḥamdihi", lb: "প্রসংসা, গুণকীর্তণ করা",e: "with his praise", b: "তার প্রশংসা সহ", i: "dengan memujiNya", f: 4, rm: "To praise or eulogize or commend someone, speak well of someone, mention someone with approbation, approve of a thing, recompense/pay someone his due, to be praiseworthy or commendable. Verb form 8: said of heat: to burn or burn fiercely, to be vehement."},
"13:13:4" : {s: 13, a: 13, w: 4, r: "ملك", t: "وَٱلْمَلَٰٓئِكَةُ", l: "مَلَك", lc: 88, tl: "wal-malāikatu", lb: "ফেরেশতা",e: "and the Angels", b: "এবং ফেরেশতারা", i: "dan Malaikat", f: 10, rm: "to rule/command/reign, be capable, to control, power/authority, king, kingdom."},
